doc.after: Cork was originally a monastic settlement reputedly founded by Saint Finbarr in the 6th century 8 Cork achieved an urban character at some point between 915 and 922 when Norseman Viking settlers founded a trading port 9 It has been proposed that like Dublin Cork was an important trading centre in the global Scandinavian trade network 10 The ecclesiastical settlement continued alongside the Viking longphort with the two developing a type of symbiotic relationship the Norsemen providing otherwise unobtainable trade goods for the monastery and perhaps also military aid 11
